# Project-local backend standards

These rules apply to **FastAPI services that do not use `omnisage_common_lib`**. Implement equivalents **inside the repository** (see `docs/project_layout.md` in this guidelines pack).

## Principles

- **Routers** are thin: auth/session `Depends`, `get_db`, validate with Pydantic, delegate to **services** only.
- **Services** own transactions (`commit`/`rollback` policy), orchestrate DAOs and HTTP clients, use `@handle_exceptions(logger=...)` (or project equivalent).
- **DAOs** own SQLAlchemy access for **one** primary model; **no** `commit`; **no** `try/except` around DB calls.
- **Schemas** (Pydantic) at API boundaries; **models** (SQLAlchemy) for persistence.

## Local modules to maintain once

| Concern | Implement in-repo |
|---------|-------------------|
| ORM base | `DeclarativeBase` subclass (e.g. `model/base.py`) |
| DB session DI | `get_db` in `deps.py` |
| API envelope | `BaseResponse[T]`, pagination types in `schema/common_schemas.py` |
| Errors | Typed exceptions + FastAPI handlers in `main.py` |
| Logging | `logging.getLogger(__name__)` or thin JSON formatter to stdout |
| Service HTTP | `httpx` wrappers in `utils/internal_http.py` with timeouts |
| Optional DAO base | `dao/base_dao.py` with `super().__init__(Model, session)` |

## Rule files (details + examples)

| Topic | File |
|-------|------|
| Routers | [router.mdc](router.mdc) |
| DAOs | [dao.mdc](dao.mdc) |
| Services | [service-function.mdc](service-function.mdc) |
| Pydantic / money | [data-validation.mdc](data-validation.mdc) |
| Logging | [logging.mdc](logging.mdc) |
| SQLAlchemy models | [sqlalchemy-model.mdc](sqlalchemy-model.mdc) |
| Outbound HTTP | [internal-http.mdc](internal-http.mdc) |

Do **not** add a dependency on OmniSage shared packages unless the team explicitly adopts them later.
